tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly with tubular involvement. Low CO₂ may indicate metabolic acidosis. Low HbA1c with glycosuria and ketonuria could reflect recent-onset or poorly controlled diabetes or another metabolic disturbance. Dyslipidemia and mild anemia are also present. Prompt nephrology and endocrinology evaluation are recommended.
